feed.title: Neds Corner - Reptiles
feed.subtitle: Area incorporating the Neds Corner property (Trust for Nature) and the adjoining Murray River frontage

entry.title: Suta spp.
entry.content: Initial ID was Suta spectabilis based on location, but body colouration and pattern suggests Suta flagellum. Mid-body scale rows were not counted.

entry.title: Ramphotyphlops spp.
entry.content: small blind snake observed active while spotlighting

entry.title: Menetia greyii
entry.content: Initially thought this was a young Morethia boulengeri but it did not have a reddish tail and on closer inspection had four fingers and five toes while Morethia have 5 digits on all limbs. See http://user-generated-content.natureshare.org.au/observations/photos/x1024/53b39862e35eb129840129c7.jpg?1404442596 for picture of juvenile Morethia boulengeri.

entry.title: Pogona vitticeps
entry.content: Sitting on a fence post by the road as we drove by.

entry.title: Pogona vitticeps, Sonchus asper subsp. asper
entry.content: Central Bearded Dragon feeding on the flowers of Sonchus asper (Sow Thistle).

entry.title: Chasmina pulchra, Gehyra variegata
entry.content: Gecko hiding behind the outside light and snacking on moths as they flew in.
